                            Forschungsumgebung / Beta maṣāḥǝft,  Akademie der Wissenschaften in Hamburg</dc:publisher><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu"/><dcterms:bibliographicCitation>PRS14016Mangest</dcterms:bibliographicCitation><dc:format>xml</dc:format><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">en</dc:language><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">gez</dc:language><dc:contributor>Alessandro Bausi</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Eugenia Sokolinski</dc:contributor><foaf:gender>male</foaf:gender><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/ontology/pers"/><foaf:name xml:lang="gez">alaqā Mangǝst</foaf:name><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><crm:P78_is_identified_by>Owner of the manuscripts was born in Diya, a small village in Enarj Enawga Waradā. He studied in different schools in the region. His expertise is in the church's music. He is one of the best oral informants in the region. He is the best expert in oral traditions about the history of the church and the country. Now he is serving as the head of the Falaga Bǝrhan Iyasus. He has "never taught Andǝmta but purchased the copied manuscripts from a 'certain farmer from a nearby village called 'Ambager'."</crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><snap:occupation/></rdf:Description><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14016Mangest/place/annotation/1"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14016Mangest"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7370FalagaB"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>Falaga Bǝrhan Iyasus</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation></rdf:RDF>